Yes — with Thymeleaf you’ll build it as normal **HTML + CSS**, then keep only the sales point list dynamic.

Use this structure:

```text
src/main/resources/templates/views/sales-points.html
src/main/resources/static/css/sales-points.css
src/main/resources/static/images/cetelem-logo.svg
src/main/resources/static/images/sales-point-hero.png
```

## `sales-points.html`

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="fr" xmlns:th="http://www.thymeleaf.org">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Choix point de vente</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" th:href="@{/css/sales-points.css}">
</head>
<body>

<main class="page">

    <section class="card">

        <div class="left-panel">
            <header class="header">
                <img class="logo" th:src="@{/images/cetelem-logo.svg}" alt="Cetelem">

                <div class="language-switch">
                    <span class="active">FR</span>
                    <span>NL</span>
                </div>
            </header>

            <div class="content">
                <h1>Connexion à<br>votre espace partenaire</h1>
                <h2>Votre point de vente</h2>

                <p class="description">
                    Vous devez choisir le point de vente dans lequel vous vous trouvez actuellement.
                </p>

                <form method="post" th:action="@{/sales-points/select}" class="sales-form">
                    <input type="hidden"
                           th:name="${_csrf.parameterName}"
                           th:value="${_csrf.token}">

                    <input type="hidden" name="appId" th:value="${appId}">

                    <div class="sales-list">
                        <label class="sales-option" th:each="sp, iter : ${salesPoints}">
                            <input type="radio"
                                   name="salesPointId"
                                   th:value="${sp.id}"
                                   th:checked="${iter.index == 0}"
                                   required>
                            <span th:text="${sp.label}">Orange Shop Bruxelles Rue Neuve</span>
                        </label>
                    </div>

                    <button type="submit" class="confirm-btn">
                        Confirmer
                        <span>→</span>
                    </button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="right-panel">
            <img th:src="@{/images/sales-point-hero.png}" alt="" class="hero-image">
        </div>

    </section>

</main>

</body>
</html>
```

## `sales-points.css`

```css
* {
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    background: #f4f4f4;
    color: #071414;
}

.page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 48px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}

.card {
    width: min(1180px, 100%);
    min-height: 720px;
    background: #ffffff;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 58% 42%;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.left-panel {
    padding: 42px 72px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
}

.header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

.logo {
    width: 140px;
    height: auto;
}

.language-switch {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
}

.language-switch span {
    color: #071414;
}

.language-switch .active {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #042f2e;
    color: white;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}

.content {
    margin-top: 92px;
    max-width: 560px;
}

h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 44px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
}

h2 {
    margin: 16px 0 0;
    font-size: 34px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    font-weight: 300;
}

.description {
    margin: 48px 0 32px;
    max-width: 420px;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: #333;
}

.sales-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
}

.sales-option {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-size: 17px;
    color: #333;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.sales-option input {
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    accent-color: #087a2f;
}

.confirm-btn {
    margin-top: 36px;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #052f2f;
    color: white;
    padding: 14px 24px;
    min-width: 140px;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.confirm-btn span {
    margin-left: 8px;
}

.right-panel {
    display: flex;
    align-items: stretch;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 80px 40px 40px 0;
}

.hero-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-top-left-radius: 28px;
}

/* Tablet */
@media (max-width: 900px) {
    .page {
        padding: 24px;
    }

    .card {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        min-height: auto;
    }

    .left-panel {
        padding: 32px;
    }

    .content {
        margin-top: 64px;
    }

    .right-panel {
        display: none;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 38px;
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 30px;
    }
}

/* Mobile */
@media (max-width: 520px) {
    .page {
        padding: 0;
        align-items: stretch;
    }

    .card {
        width: 100%;
        min-height: 100vh;
    }

    .left-panel {
        padding: 24px;
    }

    .logo {
        width: 120px;
    }

    .content {
        margin-top: 56px;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 32px;
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 26px;
    }

    .description {
        margin: 36px 0 28px;
        font-size: 15px;
    }

    .sales-option {
        font-size: 15px;
        align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .confirm-btn {
        width: 100%;
        margin-top: 32px;
    }
}
```

For the right-side mascot image, export it from Figma as PNG/SVG and save it as:

```text
src/main/resources/static/images/sales-point-hero.png
```

The dynamic part is only this:

```html
<label class="sales-option" th:each="sp, iter : ${salesPoints}">
    <input type="radio" name="salesPointId" th:value="${sp.id}">
    <span th:text="${sp.label}">Sales Point</span>
</label>
```

That keeps the design static and the data dynamic.
